Epigenetics - above the genome
 methylation causes tight chromatin (DNA + histones) packing, turning off transcription
  Barr Body - methylated X
  usually passed in to daughter in mitosis, sometimes passed down in meiosis
 agouti gene example in mice
  agouti acts as an indicator
  can be altered by maternal nutrience
   chemicals
    BPA affects offspring by hindering methylation
    soy affects offspring by promoting methylation
